â”Question:

-What happened? Explain. (after running chkdsk C: /F /X /R)

ğŸ‘‰#Answer:
Answer:

The system reports that the drive is in use and cannot be locked.

Windows asks to schedule the disk check for the next restart.

This happens because the C: drive is the active system volume. 

